Example SIS model of class `dcm` from the EpiModel package.

Source: R/data.R
sis_data.Rd

This is a deterministic SIS model where the infection parameter \(\beta = 0.2\) and the recovery/re-susceptibility parameter is \(\nu = 0.05\). The initial number of susceptible is \(S(0) = 499\) and the initial number of infectious is \(I(0)=1\). There are 100 steps. For more details, see <<http://statnet.org/tut/BasicDCMs.html#sis_model_with_sensitivity_analyses>>.

sis_data

Format

The object is a 'dcm', which is output from the EpiModel R package.

Examples

library(EpiModel)
